The broad-leafed oaks and maples embraced the Dance. As the cold descended, Ylva the wind-weaver stoked the latent sky-fire in their sap. Their canopies burst into a brilliant rebellion of crimson and gold before falling to the earth. These fallen leaves wove a thick, warm blanket over the freezing soil, allowing the deep roots to slumber safely and creating insulated burrows for the hibernating beasts below.

